    "body": "So this is only an issue coming from a `scipy.sparse` matrix, correct?\r\n\r\n```python\r\nIn [34]: pd.SparseDataFrame({\"A\": [1, np.nan, np.nan], \"B\": [0, 1, 0.], \"C\": [0, 0, 1.]}).fillna(-1)\r\nOut[34]:\r\n     A    B    C\r\n0  1.0  0.0  0.0\r\n1 -1.0  1.0  0.0\r\n2 -1.0  0.0  1.0\r\n\r\nIn [35]: pd.SparseDataFrame(spm).fillna(-1)\r\nOut[35]:\r\n     0    1    2\r\n0  1.0 -1.0 -1.0\r\n1  NaN  1.0 -1.0\r\n2  NaN -1.0  1.0\r\n```\r\n\r\nThese two should have the same output `Out[34]`?\r\n\r\ncc @sinhrks"
